					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7720063#post-4011789</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7720063/scp-4050#post-4011789</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 03 Oct 2018 04:03:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hot damn does this take a right turn after settling in.</p> <p>Nitpick:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>In the event any body of water in Helena exceeds this depth, the water is to be drained, and witnesses are to be administered Class A Amnestics.</p> </blockquote> <p>I think you need a hard stop at 'drained', and rework and clarify the final bit (or just cut it off completely), because, as-is, it reads like they're instructed to amnestize people who witness them draining water. This doesn't make a lick of sense, considering that they have ordinances in place to justify the draining. I think what is intended was something like:</p> <table class="wiki-content-table"> <tr> <td>In the event any body of water in Helena exceeds this depth, the water is to be drained. Witnesses of SCP-4050-1 are to be administered Class A Amnestics.</td> </tr> </table> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
